This place was the best gay bar we visited so far living here. We went on Tuesday and all draft beers were 3 dollars! Hard to beat considering most places serve beers for 6 or 7 dollars a piece! Air conditioning was on which is another plus. Number 1 was the server was super friendly and cute which is always a number 1 :)  Please give me a "like"!

Everything was perfectly fine until an owner, David, got behind the bar & flamed up an e-cigarette which is illegal in Hawaii. When confronted with his violation of the law, he took my drink away, refunded me $5 of my $6 cocktail & kicked me out saying "I" had too much to drink. I asked him for water & he still kicked me out. I called 911 & reported to police as it is illegal to use an e-cigarette in a bar in Hawaii.

Love Bacchus! Always have fun. Staff is great. Stop in every time I am in town. Don't miss it!

Congratulations to John & Mark (host's proprietors) for a world class Venue. my visit was between February 8th to 15th 2013. from the moment I arrived at the bar I was welcomed, and I felt completely comfortable. The customer service is outstanding at this venue. Food was available & beverage menus outstanding(everything you can wish for) Bar Staff were so "FRIENDLY,PROFESSIONAL, & very knowlegable. I wish to name the Bartender (Hunter) His service skills were Exceptional!. also their sister venue IN-Between was at the same standard. The patrons were also very nice. Thank You everyone you made my holiday so special. I definitely would recommend this venue you will have the best time there. See you all next year

Having never stepped door in this bar, I decided to stop in after a few friends asked for a suggestion for a Tuesday night  party location to chill with a gay friendly atmosphere.  This place has a unique charm all it's own.  Peaceful booths to relax after a long day, drinks are pretty reasonably priced and the wine cellar room is a must see.  The Good: Bartenders are very knowledgable on local drinks and trust me they keep them flowing.  Bar is dimly lit and can offer anyone looking for a space to unwind away from the hectic's of Waikiki will find refuge inside this bar. Bathroom is clean and well lit.  The Bad: Such a small place with only one entrance could deter those with a desire for easily escaping that creepy guy or gal you want to get away from.  Things To Try: Bartenders have a vast knowledge of the local drinks, but try The French 75, The Mind Eraser and the Bellini.  You wont be disappointed. Edit Remove Listed in: Best Happy Hour
